{{Infobox person | name = Alberto Bombassei | image = Alberto Bombassei daticamera.jpg | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1940|10}} | birth_place = [[Vicenza]], Italy | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | restingplace = | nationality = Italian | religion = | ethnicity = | residence = [[Bergamo]], Italy | education = | alma mater = | occupation = | title = chairman and president of Brembo | term = | predecessor = | successor = | known for = Owner of Brembo | boards = | salary = €5,200,000 (2016)<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=675202&privcapId=882929 |title=Stocks |publisher=[[Bloomberg L.P.|Bloomberg]] |date= |accessdate=2017-01-23}}</ref> | networth = US$1.6 billion (August 2018)<ref name="Forbes" /> | spouse = married | parents = [[Emilio Bombassei]] | children = 2 | relations = | website = }}
'''Alberto Bombassei''' (born October 1940)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/officers/HQgUOVdkk7IM52Ylf_s58i35L58/appointments |title=Alberto BOMBASSEI - Personal Appointments (free information from Companies House) |website=Beta.companieshouse.gov.uk |date= |accessdate=2017-01-23}}</ref> is an Italian [[billionaire]] businessman, the chairman and president of [[Brembo]], an Italian manufacturer of automotive brake systems.<ref name="Forbes">{{cite web|title=The World's Billionaires: Alberto Bombassei|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/alberto-bombassei/|website=Forbes|accessdate=23 January 2017}}</ref> He controls 53.5% of Brembo.<ref name="bloomberg1">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2014-01-23/brembo-chairman-becomes-billionaire-on-brakes-for-porsche |title=Brembo Chairman Becomes Billionaire on Brakes for Porsche |publisher=[[Bloomberg L.P.|Bloomberg]] |date=2014-01-23 |accessdate=2017-01-23}}</ref>
He was born in [[Vicenza]], Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atlantia.it/it/pdf/ListaCRTENG.pdf |format=PDF |title=Atlantia - Rome : ATLANTIA SpA ORDINARY GENERAL MEETING of 9 April 2010; |language=it |website=Atlantia.it |accessdate=2017-01-23}}</ref> His father [[Emilio Bombassei]] co-founded Brembo in 1961 with [[Italo Breda]], and in 1975, [[Enzo Ferrari]] asked the company to provide braking systems for his Formula 1 racing cars.<ref name="bloomberg1"/>
He is married with two children, and lives in [[Bergamo]], Italy.<ref name="Forbes" />
