{{Infobox person |name = Cory Vidanes |image = |caption = Cory Vidanes |birth_name = María Socorro Valenzuela-Vidanes |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1962|05|15}} |birth_place = [[Philippines]] |other_names = CVV |known_for = |occupation = Chief Operating Officer for broadcast of [[ABS-CBN Corporation]] |spouse = [[Bobet Vidanes]] |influences = |alma_mater = [[Ateneo de Manila University]] |yearsactive = 1982–present }}
'''Cory Vidanes''' (born '''María Socorro Valenzuela-Vidanes''')<ref>{{cite web|title=ABS-CBN Corp (ABS.PS)|publisher=[[Reuters]]|accessdate=26 February 2013|url=https://www.reuters.com/finance/stocks/companyOfficers?symbol=ABS.PS}}</ref> is a [[Filipino people|Filipina]] executive and currently serves as Chief Operating Officer of broadcast<ref name=ABS>{{cite web|title=Ma. Socorro V. Vidanes|url=http://ir.abs-cbn.com/Portals/_default/Skins/IR/ko/MSV.html?iframe=true&width=600&height=320|publisher=[[ABS-CBN]]|accessdate=26 February 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Belen|first=Crispina M.|title=Cory Vidanes, new channel head of ABS-CBN|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/articles/200540/cory-vidanes-new-channel-head-abscbn|work=[[Manila Bulletin]]|accessdate=26 February 2013|date=28 March 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Cory Vidanes named new ABS-CBN Channel head|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/entertainment/03/20/09/cory-vidanes-named-new-abs-cbn-channel-head|publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]]|accessdate=26 February 2013|date=20 March 2009}}</ref> for [[ABS-CBN]], the largest media conglomerate in the [[Philippines]].
== Personal life == Vidanes first attended [[Assumption Antipolo]] and later [[Ateneo de Manila University]], where she obtained her Bachelor of Arts in Communication.<ref name="ABS"/><ref>{{cite web|last=Puyat|first=Leah|title=The other 'Tita Cory'|url=http://www.philstar.com/sunday-life/2012/07/08/825426/other-tita-cory|work=[[The Philippine Star]]|accessdate=26 February 2013|date=8 July 2012}}</ref>
Vidanes is married to [[Bobet Vidanes]], a Filipino television director.
== Career == In 1982, Vidanes started her broadcast career for the [[Banahaw Broadcasting Corporation]] (BBC-2) as a production assistant for the shows Big Ike's Happening and Vilma in Person (VIP).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://journal.com.ph/entertainment/showbiz/vilma-tikom-ang-bibig-sa-luis-angel-breakup|title=Vilma, tikom ang bibig sa Luis-Angel breakup|publisher=''Journal Online''|last=Alejandrino|first=Nel|date=January 30, 2016|accessdate=February 1, 2016}}</ref> She started working with ABS-CBN when the network reopened in 1986 as an Associate Producer. She also served as a Managing Director for ABS-CBN TV Production from 2001 to 2009. She was responsible for the conceptualization, production and management of all TV Entertainment programs on ABS-CBN Channel 2. She was appointed Head of Channel 2 Mega Manila Management for ABS-CBN effective in 2009 after Charo Santos-Concio promoted to become president and COO of the company.<ref name="ABS"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Vidanes, Ma. Socorro|url=https://www.reuters.com/finance/stocks/officerProfile?symbol=ABS.PS&officerId=508743|publisher=[[Reuters]]|accessdate=26 February 2013}}</ref>
In 2016, Vidanes was appointed as the chief operating officer for broadcast division of ABS-CBN effective February 1. This happened one month after the appointment of [[Carlo Katigbak]] as the network's new president and CEO.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abscbnpr.com/cory-vidanes-appointed-abs-cbns-coo-of-broadcast/|title=CORY VIDANES APPOINTED ABS-CBN’S COO OF BROADCAST|publisher=''ABS-CBN PR''|date=January 29, 2016|accessdate=January 29, 2016}}</ref>
Under her position as a COO of broadcast, she will also manage the development of new concepts for ABS-CBN channel 2 and ABS-CBN TVplus channels Yey, CineMo, and Knowledge Channel, together with ABS-CBN CCO Charo Santos-Concio.
