'''Turkish Cypriot Chamber of Commerce''' ('''''Kıbrıs Türk Ticaret Odası''''' in Turkish) (KTTO) was founded in Nicosia, Cyprus, in 1958 and represents businesses in [[North Cyprus]]. KTTO is a [[Chamber of commerce|public law chamber]] and membership is obligatory for businesses. KTTO has around 3000 members in 2011.
KTTO was founded in 1958 when Cyprus was still a British colony. The Chamber continued to exist when [[Cyprus dispute|Cyprus became independent]] in 1960.
